  "original_title": "6 \u0bae\u0bbe\u0ba4 \u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd 5 \u0bae\u0bc1\u0bb1\u0bc8 \u0baa\u0bb8\u0bcd \u0b95\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0ba3\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0b85\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "5 times increase in bus fares over a period of 6 months",
      "author": "Vishnu",
      "body_lines": [
        "The bus fare hike has been increased by 21.85 per cent with effect from midnight on Thursday the 30th based on 12 factors including the annual bus fare revision and fuel price hike.",
        "According to Milan Mirunda, Director General of the National Transport Commission, the minimum bus fare has been fixed at 40 rupees.",
        "Bus fares have been revised five times in the last 6 months due to fuel price hike alone.",
        "The private bus owners associations have mentioned that the current fare revision is not satisfactory.",
        "The new fare revision has set the minimum bus fare at Rs 40 and the maximum bus fare at Rs 2948.",
        "The National Transport Commission has announced that the new fare revision schedule will be displayed on buses.",
        "The Director General of the National Transport Commission (NTC) made the remarks while addressing a media briefing at the Government Information Department yesterday.",
        "During the last 6 months alone, the bus fare has been revised 4 times in line with the fuel price hike.",
        "The private and public bus associations presented several ideas regarding the annual bus fare revision.",
        "The bus fare has been revised with effect from 11am yesterday with 11 basic factors including fuel price hike.",
        "There was no consensus among the unions on the proposals put forward by the union to increase bus fares in line with fuel prices.",
        "The ideas put forward by the private bus unions that bus fares should be increased by 20 or 30 per cent are not acceptable.",
        "Based on various factors, it has been decided to increase the bus fare by 21.85 percent and the minimum bus fare has been fixed at Rs 40.",
        "Public commuters using the bus service can report any inconveniences they encounter to the National Transport Commission by calling 1955.",
        "He said that due to the shortage of fuel, the public transport service is currently restricted to focus on a few issues.",
        "The bus fare has been revised five times in the six months since its completion.",
        "Accordingly, bus fares were revised by 17.44 percent in January, 15 percent in March, 35 percent in April, and 19.5 percent in May.",
        "The bus fare has been increased by 21.85 per cent based on the increase in fuel prices and the annual fare revision last month.",
        "The bus fare has not been revised in line with fuel prices. Private bus operators have expressed dissatisfaction that the current pricing is not satisfactory."
      ],
